quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  64,10,"And those who disbelieved and denied Our signs, are the people of the fire – to remain in it forever; and what a wretched outcome!"
  64,11,"No misfortune befalls except by Allah’s command; and Allah will guide the heart of whoever accepts faith in Him; and Allah knows all things."
  64,12,"And obey Allah and obey His Noble Messenger; then if you turn away, know that the duty upon Our Noble Messenger is only to plainly convey."
  64,13,"Allah – there is none worthy of worship except Him; and only upon Allah must the Muslims rely."
  64,14,"O People who Believe! Some of your wives and children are your enemies, therefore be wary of them; and if you pardon and overlook and forgive, then indeed Allah is Oft Forgiving, Most Merciful."
  64,15,"Your wealth and your children are just a test; and with Allah is a tremendous reward."
  64,16,"Therefore fear Allah as much as possible, and heed the commands, and obey, and spend in Allah’s cause, for your own good; and whoever is rescued from the greed of his own soul – is they who will be successful."
  64,17,"If you lend an excellent loan to Allah, He will double it for you and forgive you; and Allah is Most Appreciative, Most Forbearing."
  64,18,"The All Knowing of all things hidden and visible, the Most Honourable, the Wise."
